{"name": "pyobjc-framework-exceptionhandling", "metadata": {"name": "pyobjc-framework-ExceptionHandling", "version": "10.3.2", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 5 - Production/Stable", "Environment :: Console", "Environment :: MacOS X :: Cocoa", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Natural Language :: English", "Operating System :: MacOS :: MacOS X", "Programming Language :: Objective C", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3 :: Only", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.13", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9", "Programming Language :: Python :: Implementation :: CPython", "Topic :: Software Development :: Libraries :: Python Modules", "Topic :: Software Development :: User Interfaces"], "home_page": "https://github.com/ronaldoussoren/pyobjc", "license": "MIT License", "documentation_url": "https://pyobjc.readthedocs.io/en/latest/", "dependencies": ["pyobjc-core", "pyobjc-framework-Cocoa"], "summary": "Wrappers for the framework ExceptionHandling on macOS", "upload_time": 1732974469}, "documentation": ["\nWrappers for the \"ExceptionHandling\" framework on macOS. The ExceptionHandling\nframework provides facilities for monitoring and debugging exceptional\nconditions in Cocoa programs.\n\nPyObjC also provides low-level debugging utilities beyond the core\nExceptionHandling framework in the module ``PyObjCTools.Debugging``.\n\nThese wrappers don't include documentation, please check Apple's documentation\nfor information on how to use this framework and PyObjC's documentation\nfor general tips and tricks regarding the translation between Python\nand (Objective-)C frameworks\n\n\nProject links\n-------------\n\n* `Documentation <https://pyobjc.readthedocs.io/en/latest/>`_\n\n* `Issue Tracker <https://github.com/ronaldoussoren/pyobjc/issues>`_\n\n* `Repository <https://github.com/ronaldoussoren/pyobjc/>`_\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "PyObjCTools.Debugging", "documentation": ["Low level debugging helper for PyObjC.\n\nAllows you to log Python and ObjC (via atos) stack traces for NSExceptions\nraised.\n\nGeneral guidelines for use:\n\n- It's typically only useful when you log EVERY exception, because Foundation\n  and AppKit will swallow most of them.  This means that you should never\n  use this module in a release build.\n\n- Typical use involves only calling installExceptionHandler or\n  installVerboseExceptionHandler.  It may be removed at any time by calling\n  removeDebuggingHandler."], "functions": [{"name": "PyObjCTools.Debugging.isPythonException", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "exception", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "PyObjCTools.Debugging.nsLogPythonException", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "exception", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "PyObjCTools.Debugging._run_atos", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "stack", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "PyObjCTools.Debugging.nsLogObjCException", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "exception", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "PyObjCTools.Debugging.installExceptionHandler", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "verbosity", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "mask", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Install the exception handling delegate that will log every exception\nmatching the given mask with the given verbosity."]}, {"name": "PyObjCTools.Debugging.installPythonExceptionHandler", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Install a verbose exception handling delegate that logs every exception\nraised.\n\nWill log only Python stack traces, if available."]}, {"name": "PyObjCTools.Debugging.installVerboseExceptionHandler", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Install a verbose exception handling delegate that logs every exception\nraised.\n\nWill log both Python and ObjC stack traces, if available."]}, {"name": "PyObjCTools.Debugging.removeExceptionHandler", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Remove the current exception handler delegate"]}, {"name": "PyObjCTools.Debugging.handlerInstalled", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Is an exception handler delegate currently installed?"]}], "variables": [{"name": "PyObjCTools.Debugging.DEFAULTMASK", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "PyObjCTools.Debugging.EVERYTHINGMASK", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "PyObjCTools.Debugging._atos_command", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "PyObjCTools.Debugging.LOGSTACKTRACE", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "PyObjCTools.Debugging.DEFAULTVERBOSITY", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "PyObjCTools.Debugging.PyObjCDebuggingDelegate", "bases": ["NSObject"], "methods": [{"name": "PyObjCTools.Debugging.PyObjCDebuggingDelegate.initWithVerbosity_", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "verbosity", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "PyObjCTools.Debugging.PyObjCDebuggingDelegate.exceptionHandler_shouldLogException_mask_", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "sender", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "exception", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "aMask", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "PyObjCTools.Debugging.PyObjCDebuggingDelegate.exceptionHandler_shouldHandleException_mas